This paper proposes a novel learning method for image classification, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The method involves training a model to output the mixing ratio of two images, which is a machine learning (cs.LG) approach. The paper also discusses the use of convolutional neural networks, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed method involves generating between-class images, which is a technique that could potentially be applied to other domains, such as natural language processing (cs.NE) or multimedia (cs.MM).
